Global Youtube Statistic Analysis¶

I. Introduction¶

In today's digital era, YouTube has transcended its origins as a platform for user-generated content to become a global phenomenon, revolutionizing the way we consume information and entertainment. With an ever-expanding universe of creators, audiences, and content, YouTube is a dynamic ecosystem that shapes modern media, entertainment, and marketing landscapes. This analysis endeavors to explore the multifaceted world of YouTube through a comprehensive dataset, which includes details on top creators' subscriber counts, video views, upload frequency, country of origin, earnings, and more.

The significance of this endeavor lies in unraveling the secrets behind YouTube's immense success, the strategies employed by top creators, and the emerging trends that influence content creation and audience engagement. By leveraging this rich dataset, we aim to provide actionable insights that can drive decision-making, foster innovation, and enable stakeholders to tap into the full potential of the YouTube platform.

II. Analysis¶

1.Business Objective/Problem¶

Through the dataset including top 10 Youtubers in the world, we will conduct a deep explorationary data analysis to get insights that can help us give the best answers to the following business questions and satisfy our business objectives:

  1. What are top 10 Youtubers who have the highest amount of views?

  2. Does it mean that a Youtube channel owning a high number of subscribers is associated with a high amount of views?

  3. Does it mean that a Youtube channel owning a high total of uploads will lead to a high number of subscribers and amount of views

  4. What are some categories of Youtube channels which have the most uploads?

  5. How many channels are there in each category?

  6. What are some Youtube user trends throughout the number of subscribers and the amount of views in each category?

  7. What are some interesting interaction and behaviors of users in those catgories. (measured by total views of per user)

  8. Does the content (key terms) in the name of YouTube channels affect user views?

  9. What countries do those top 10 youtubers come from?

    9.1 What is the unemployment rate?

    9.2 What is the rate of high education attainment of each country?

    9.3 What is the rate of urban population in each country?

  10. When were most successful Youtube Channel created ?

  11. What are the trending content creactivity of each chanel over the time?

  12. What is the posibility of generating average earnings per month in each category?

  13. Does it mean that a higher amount of views will lead to a higher earning?

2. Data Preparing¶

Key Features: Rank: Position of the YouTube channel based on the number of subscribers Youtuber

Population: Name of the YouTube channel

subscribers: Number of subscribers to the channel

video views : Total views across all videos on the channel

category : Category or niche of the channel

Title : Title of the YouTube channel

uploads : Total number of videos uploaded on the channel

Country : Country where the YouTube channel originates

Abbreviation : Abbreviation of the country

channel_type : Type of the YouTube channel (e.g., individual, brand)

video_views_rank : Ranking of the channel based on total video views

country_rank : Ranking of the channel based on the number of subscribers within its country

channel_type_rank : Ranking of the channel based on its type (individual or brand)

video_views_for_the_last_30_days : Total video views in the last 30 days

lowest_monthly_earnings : Lowest estimated monthly earnings from the channel

highest_monthly_earnings : Highest estimated monthly earnings from the channel

lowest_yearly_earnings : Lowest estimated yearly earnings from the channel

highest_yearly_earnings : Highest estimated yearly earnings from the channel

subscribers_for_last_30_days : Number of new subscribers gained in the last 30

days created_year : Year when the YouTube channel was created

created_month : Month when the YouTube channel was created

created_date : Exact date of the YouTube channel's creation

Gross tertiary education enrollment (%) : Percentage of the population enrolled in tertiary education in the country

Population: Total population of the country

Unemployment rate : Unemployment rate in the country

Urban_population : Percentage of the population living in urban areas

Latitude : Latitude coordinate of the country's location

Longitude : Longitude coordinate of the country's location

From the correlation matrix table, Subscribers and Views have a high correlation rate up to 82%. The scatter plot chart shows in more detail the positive relationship between these two variables (the more subscribers a YouTube channel has, the more views it will have). Looking at the scatter plot chart, the distribution of the majority of data is concentrated in a range significantly lower than the top 10 mentioned in question 1, while only a few channels have a larger number of subscribers and views than the rest. Specifically, through the histogram chart, the data shows that up to 95% of YouTube channels have less than 46 million subscribers and less than 28 billion views.

=> This leads to the conclusion that:

  • In fact, there is a significant positive relationship between subscribers and views. At the same time, this also implies that only a few channels truly outperform the rest in terms of success (measured based on the number of Subscribers and Views).

  • So the question is what factors contribute to the success of a YouTube channel?

  • With extremely low correlation rates (0.9% and 17% respectively) and inconsistent data dispersion, we can conclude that a YouTube channel with many uploads doesn't mean that the channel will receive more subscribers and views.   • News and Politics is a content group specializing in posting videos about current events and politics including news, reports, interviews, discussions and other TV programs.The content of this section requires accuracy and continuous updating of new information, which means there is no tendency to replay them. In fact, producing content in this category often requires forces with large resources. These can be state-owned and managed organizations or high-level agencies that have an influential voice in the public for the purpose of providing reliable and useful information to viewers. This is one of YouTube's exceptions in having the highest number of videos posted regardless of views and followers.

Anyone can capitalize on the content in this category because of its diversity of topics, thereby increasing the number of Video Uploads to approximately the highest. YouTube channels in this category are often heavily influenced by views and subscribers, which is almost the significant attribution to promoting and maintaining the development of channels built by individuals.

  • Currently, the trend of producing content in the form of short videos from TikTok, Reels of Instagram, Short-form videos of Facebook,... This content model can generate a lot of Uploads in a short time but still attract a large number of modern viewers. Analysis: The category 'Show' leads with a significantly higher average view-to-subscriber ratio, surpassing Pets & Animals by over 27%. This comes as a surprise considering its previously modest subscription and view numbers (512 million subscribers and 432 billion views). In contrast, the two leading categories in YouTube user trends have relatively average view-to-subscriber ratios: 602 for Music and 493 for Entertainment.

A high view-to-subscriber ratio indicates:

Dedicated Fan Base: Subscribers frequently return to watch new content, demonstrating a strong connection between content creators and their audience. High-Quality Content Draws Engagement: Engaging and timely topics leave a positive impression on subscribers, encouraging them to watch regularly, revisit videos, and thereby accumulate more views per subscriber.

Conversely, categories with low view-to-subscriber ratios may have several reasons:

Viral Content Focus: Channels may have a few viral videos that attract a large number of views at one time, but fail to sustain this across all uploaded content, thus not converting views into subscribers consistently.

Broad Appeal: Widely appealing content is often shared or viewed across multiple platforms besides YouTube, attracting views from casual viewers who may not necessarily subscribe.

Search-Friendly Content: Channels creating content that answers common questions (e.g., Howto & Style, Travel & Events, Science & Technology) or covers popular topics tend to have higher discoverability through YouTube or Google searches. However, once viewers find the information they need, they may not feel the need to subscribe.

These insights underscore how viewer behavior on YouTube is influenced by content quality, engagement strategies, and the ability to maintain viewer interest over time. Channels that effectively nurture subscriber loyalty and consistently produce compelling, relevant content tend to achieve higher engagement metrics.

Analysis

The most prominent words in the Word Cloud chart above, such as Music, Kids, Songs, Entertainment, Nursery Rhymes, and Record, are highly relevant to the YouTube channel trends discussed in previous analyses like Music, Entertainment, and Shows.

The close correlation between the characters in YouTube channel names and their categories can be attributed to several factors:

Clear Brand Identification: Creators often want their channel names to reflect the type of content they produce. This helps potential users quickly understand the focus of the channel. A name that aligns well with the content enhances brand clarity and sets audience expectations.

Recognizability: Channels with keywords in their names that are also key terms in their category listings can improve the channel's visibility in search results.

Consistency between Name and Content: When a channel's name directly relates to its category, it provides a cohesive experience for viewers. For example, a channel named 'Action Movies' in the Movies category aligns with what users expect based on its name.

These factors underscore how the choice of words in YouTube channel names can influence brand perception, discoverability, and user engagement. Channels that effectively utilize keywords related to their content categories can enhance their appeal to target audiences and attract more views.

6. Conclusion:¶

There are numerous factors that determine the success of a YouTube channel, and this analysis is based solely on the provided variables. More comprehensive data is needed to offer deeper and more useful insights for those aiming to engage with the platform.

Key Factors for YouTube Success and Trends from the Dataset:

***Determinants of Success:

YouTube channels with a strong subscriber base tend to attract more video views. Building a loyal subscriber base requires time and the effectiveness of the content provided by the channel creator. This is why channels established during key periods often achieve significant success. Overall, it is a continuous process of persistence and creativity.

Loyal Followers:

Content Selection: Categories such as Entertainment, Music, Gaming, and Comedy dominate in terms of popularity. Channels producing content in these categories often attract more viewers, especially in entertainment and music. Meanwhile, Education and How to & Style consistently hold a respectable position on the ranking, underscoring the essential nature of these content types. Shows have the highest view-to-subscriber ratio, indicating a high number of loyal followers and high-quality content. However, some categories featuring viral or search-friendly content are not performing as effectively, as they only attract unsustainable viewership. For example, the Travel & Events category illustrates this trend.

Income Sources Beyond Views:

Although there is a positive correlation between views and income, this relationship is not particularly strong. A channel's income can depend on several factors, including engagement levels, video duration, and ad placement—factors not reflected in this dataset, which limits the ability to identify the most effective income sources on the platform. However, based on the available data, shows appear to offer significant earning potential, despite music and entertainment being more popular categories.

Quality Over Quantity:

As analyzed earlier, uploading more videos does not necessarily result in more followers or views. Leading YouTubers prioritize the quality of their video content, as content is the most crucial factor. Videos must provide value to viewers, be engaging and interesting, and meet the needs of the target audience to drive interaction and satisfaction.

Consistency:

There is a strong connection between video content, channel category, and channel name. This consistency helps viewers easily find the content they need, increasing the likelihood of being recommended during searches and helping the channel reach a broader audience.

*** User Trends Across the Most Successful YouTube Channels:

Historically, during the first half of YouTube's development, music dominated user trends, maintaining prominence for six consecutive years (from 2007 to 2012). In the second half and continuing to the present, user trends have gradually shifted towards entertainment content, with the Entertainment category becoming increasingly popular.

Music and entertainment are currently the two most popular categories on the platform, consistently leading in subscriber numbers and view counts. However, the Show category has the highest view frequency per subscriber, indicating that Show content is particularly effective at attracting and retaining engaged viewers who are likely to revisit the content.

The common thread among these three categories is their ability to create diverse entertainment experiences for users. This highlights the significant role of entertainment in driving user engagement on YouTube.

*** Recommendations for Building an Effective YouTube Channel in the Future:

Identify Content and Target Audience: As the world evolves and topics diversify, finding a content niche that aligns with your creative strengths and identifying a related target audience is the first step to establishing a presence on the platform.

Quality Content: As emphasized throughout the analysis, content quality is paramount. A channel featuring engaging videos that meet viewer needs is more likely to convert views into subscriptions.

Viewer Interaction: Engaging with viewers by responding to comments, interacting on social media, and building a supportive community is crucial for developing a loyal subscriber base.

Cross-Platform Sharing: Sharing videos and content (release schedules, demo videos, teasers, etc.) on linked social media platforms can enhance visibility and reach targeted audiences.

SEO (Search Engine Optimization): Optimizing both video content and descriptions can improve the likelihood of appearing in YouTube search results.

Personal Branding: Continuously updating and expanding your knowledge in your primary content area is essential for in-depth development. Leveraging your creativity to produce unique and standout content is key to distinguishing your channel from others.

Time and Patience: Building a channel and amassing a large, loyal audience is a long-term process. Persistence and continuous effort to stay current with trends are vital qualities for any aspiring YouTuber.
